  "text": "A Grassmannian manifold, Gr(N, M ) is a set of N −dimensional subspaces in R M , where each subspace maps to a unique point on the manifold [CITATION_1] . Each point in Gr(N, M ) can be conveniently represented using an M × N orthonormal matrix which forms a basis for that subspace. Given two points in a Grassmannian, represented by their orthonormal bases, A and B of size M × N , there are several distance measures that can be computed between them. The distance measured along the geodesic is the Grassmann distance and can be computed by decomposing A T B using its SVD and obtain-",
